events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Amari Cooper caught two touchdown passes from AJ McCarron and Christion Jones returned a kickoff 99 yards for another score, leading No. 1 Alabama to a 33-14 victory over Mississippi Saturday night.

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Avery Patterson didn't believe the halftime talk from Oregon's coaches was suitable to print.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon rides big 3rd quarter to win vs. Wazzu

events.name: Towson Tigers at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Zach Mettenberger connected with Odell Beckham Jr. five times for 128 yards and two touchdowns, and No. 3 LSU overcame nagging offensive sloppiness in a 38-22 victory over overmatched but feisty Towson on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 3 LSU struggles to down Towson

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: EJ Manuel threw for 242 yards and a touchdown, helping No. 4 Florida State remain unbeaten with a 30-17 victory over South Florida on Saturday night.

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Todd Gurley ran for three touchdowns and Keith Marshall added two as No. 5 Georgia recovered after blowing a 17-point lead to beat Tennessee 51-44 on Saturday in the highest-scoring game ever between the SEC rivals.

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Marcus Lattimore ran for two touchdowns and Connor Shaw passed for another in the second half as No. 6 South Carolina scored 31 straight points for a 38-17 victory against Kentucky on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lattimore (2 TDs), S. Carolina rally by Kentucky

events.name: Baylor Bears at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw for 656 yards and tied a Big 12 record with eight touchdown passes to lead No. 9 West Virginia to a 70-63 win over No. 25 Baylor on Saturday.

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: David Ash threw three touchdown passes to Jaxon Shipley and Joe Bergeron scored on a 2-yard run with 29 seconds left to lift No. 12 Texas to a 41-36 win against Oklahoma State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late TD lifts Texas past Okla. St.

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Braxton Miller threw for 179 yards and ran for 130, and No. 14 Ohio State held off No. 20 Michigan State 17-16 on Saturday, giving Urban Meyer a win in his first Big Ten game as Buckeyes coach.

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at SMU Mustangs

headlines.description: Casey Pachall threw two touchdown passes, Jason Verrett had two interceptions and No. 15 TCU extended its FBS-best winning streak to 12 games by beating SMU 24-16 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU wins 12th game in a row by handling SMU

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw for 367 yards and three touchdowns and ran in another himself as No. 17 Clemson beat Boston College 45-31 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boyd runs for score, leads Clemson

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Oregon State beat Arizona 38-35.

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles

headlines.description: Senorise Perry rushed for 118 yards and two touchdowns, Jeremy Wright added 84 rushing yards and No. 19 Louisville rallied to beat Southern Miss 21-17 in a downpour on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 19 Louisville rallies to defeat Southern Miss

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Taylor Martinez guided four straight scoring drives against a tiring Wisconsin defense in the second half to lead No. 22 Nebraska's comeback from a 17-point deficit to defeat the Badgers 30-27 on Saturday night.

events.name: Boise State Broncos at New Mexico Lobos

headlines.description: Joe Southwick passed for 311 yards and three touchdowns and Timmy Smith knocked down a fourth-down pass with two minutes to go Saturday to help No. 24 Boise State beat New Mexico 32-29 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Southwick, Boise St. stave off New Mexico rally

events.name: Buffalo Bulls at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Connecticut running backs Lyle McCombs and Martin Hyppolite combined for 157 yards rushing and two touchdowns to lead Connecticut to a 24-17 win over Buffalo on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCombs, Hyppolite lead UConn past Buffalo

events.name: Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Benny Cunningham rushed for 217 yards and five touchdowns Saturday to lead Middle Tennessee State to a 49-28 win at Georgia Tech.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham (5 TDs), MTSU take down Ga. Tech

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Kain Colter ran for 161 yards and four touchdowns, and Northwestern set a school record with 704 yards of total offense in a 44-29 victory over Indiana on Saturday in both teams' Big Ten opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northwestern sets yards mark, beats Indiana

events.name: Stony Brook Seawolves at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: Stony Brook 23, Army 3

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Matt McGloin threw for 211 yards and a touchdown and ran for two more scores to lead Penn State to a 35-7 win over Illinois Saturday in the schools' Big Ten opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: McGloin, Penn State romp in Big Ten opener

events.name: Missouri Tigers at UCF Knights

headlines.description: Marcus Murphy returned a punt 66 yards for a touchdown and James Franklin added an 80-yard touchdown pass as Missouri ground out a 21-16 win over Central Florida on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mizzou escapes UCF using Murphy's punt return

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Mark Weisman ran for 177 yards, 155 in the first half, to lead Iowa to a 31-13 win over Minnesota on Saturday and give the Hawkeyes possession of the Floyd of Rosedale bronze pig trophy.
headlines.shortLinkText: Weisman, Iowa hand rival Minnesota first loss

headlines.description: Kent St. 45, Ball St. 43

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Stephen Morris threw for a school and ACC-record 566 yards and five touchdowns, the last of those a 62-yard strike to Phillip Dorsett with 19 seconds left, and Miami beat North Carolina State 44-37 on Saturday.

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel threw for a school-record 453 yards and three touchdowns and ran for another score to lead Texas A&M over Arkansas 58-10 on Saturday for the Aggies' first Southeastern Conference win.
headlines.shortLinkText: A&M nabs 1st SEC win with record Manziel

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Backup quarterback Anthony Boone scored on a 4-yard touchdown run with 11:35 left, and Duke beat Wake Forest 34-27 on Saturday for its first win in the series since 1999.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boone's late TD helps Duke end skid vs. Wake
